{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":463476,"duration_api_ms":443834,"num_turns":5,"result":"Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/12-0b9bd80/feedback.md`. Here's the summary:\n\n## Four root causes across 17 failures\n\n**Pattern 1 (12 files) — Ingredient bullets pass all hard filters**\n- `looksLikeIngredient` is English-only and only matches explicit measurement units. Polish units (`łyżka`, `szklanka`), compact metric (`100g`, `50g`), and no-unit ingredients (`Salt to taste`, `Sól do smaku`, `2 jajka`) all slip through.\n- Lines starting with `- ` (bullet) aren't caught by `startsWithNumber` (which only checks `/^\\s*\\d/`). No bullet-marker filter exists.\n\n**Pattern 2 (Mozzarella Sticks) — `INGREDIENTS` returned instead of title**\n- The `isSubHeader` guard assumes `sortedCaps[0]` is the recipe title. When the layout is `INGREDIENTS → TITLE → ingredients`, the actual title is in sortedCaps[1], its next line contains `tbsp` → classified as sub-header → `INGREDIENTS` wins.\n\n**Pattern 3 (4 files) — Multiple ingredient lines joined with `+`**\n- Repeated consecutive ingredient lines (e.g. two `- 100g butter` lines) produce a valid 2-line join candidate that passes hard filters. When zero ALL_CAPS headings survive threshold, the multi-title guard keeps all survivors and joins them with `+`.\n\n**Common theme:** Once the correct ALL_CAPS title is demoted or fails threshold, the fallback pool consists of whatever ingredient lines weren't caught by the narrow `looksLikeIngredient` check — and the embedding scores don't reliably prefer titles over unrecognized ingredient patterns.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"d3c78e08-9dc3-489d-8b45-de39a42f3486","total_cost_usd":0.71175565,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":49118,"cache_read_input_tokens":157399,"output_tokens":22731,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":491